{"word":"H3384 - יָרָה - yârâh - yaw-raw' - Archer","slug":"H3384","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יָרָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yârâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yaw-raw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Archer"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E8;&#x05D0;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D9;&#x05E8;&#x05D4; - ya&#x0302;ra&#x0302;h  ya&#x0302;ra&#x0302;'</b> - <i>yaw-raw', yaw-raw'</i><p/>A primitive root; properly to <i>flow</i> as water (that is, to <i>rain</i>); transitively to <i>lay</i> or <i>throw</i> (especially an arrow, that is, to <i>shoot</i>); figuratively to <i>point</i> out (as if by <i>aiming</i> the finger), to <i>teach: - </i> (+) archer, cast, direct, inform, instruct, lay, shew, shoot, teach (-er, -ing), through."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3138\">H3138</a>, <a href=\"#/H3139\">H3139</a>, <a href=\"#/H3140\">H3140</a>, <a href=\"#/H3385\">H3385</a>, <a href=\"#/H3400\">H3400</a>, <a href=\"#/H3404\">H3404</a>, <a href=\"#/H4175\">H4175</a>, <a href=\"#/H4176\">H4176</a>, <a href=\"#/H8451\">H8451</a>, <a href=\"#/H8452\">H8452</a>"}]}